NOTICE OF ASSOCIATION ASSESSMENT LIEN
PURSUANT TO A.R.S. $ 33-1256 OR $ 33-1807
Palm Valley Community Center Association, Inc ., an Arizona Nonprofit Corporation ("Association"), hereby gives notice
that, pursuant to A.R.S. $ 33-1256 or $ 33-1807, the Association has a lien for assessments (and potentially other
amounts allowed by law) pursuant to the Association's Declaration of Covenants and Restrictions ("Declaration"), which
was recorded as Document Number 2002-0905012 on September 4, 2002 in the Maricopa County Recorder's Office
under Article 6, Section 6.1.
1. The legal description of the unit against which the lien exists (the "Unit") is Lot 59, OF CAMELOT AT PALM
VALLEY, according to the plat of record in the office of the County Recorder of Maricopa County, Arizona,
recorded in Book 766 of Maps, Page 27 and Certificate of Correction recorded in Document No.
2005-1384618 of Official Records.
a. Commonly known as: 14431 W Coronado Road
Goodyear, AZ 85395
2. The owner of the Unit, according to the Association's records, is:
Valentin Ruiz
3. The amount of the lien, as of May 31, 2022, is: $492.00.
The amount of the lien may increase as set forth in the Declaration and A.R.S. 5 33-1256 or $ 33-1807
until it is satisfied in full.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand this
1St day of June
2022.
Jonathan Sutter, the Managing Agent of Palm Valley Community
Center Association, Inc.
State of Arizona
County of Maricopa
